  "scenario": {
    "setting": "A mid-cap industrial equipment manufacturer (FY revenue ~$800M).\nMonthly controller packages include: revenue by channel, AR aging\n(current/30/60/90/120+ days), DSO calculation, gross margin by\nproduct line, cash flow from operations, and internal auditor\nfootnotes. The CFO is progressively manipulating revenue recognition\nthrough channel stuffing, bill-and-hold arrangements, and eventually\nround-tripping with a distributor. Financial ratios drift before\nthe fraud becomes overt.\n",
